Sentencas: The effect of SO2 content in air on degradation of a La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 (LSCF6428) cathode for solid oxide fuel cells was investigated at T = 1073 K for 24 h by setting the concentration of SO2 to 0.1, 1, 10, and 100 ppm.
Titulo: Sulfur Poisoning on La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 Cathode for SOFCs

Sentencas: The degradation of the LSCF6428 cathode became more significant with increasing SO2 concentrations due to the increase of cathode polarization resistance.
Titulo: Sulfur Poisoning on La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 Cathode for SOFCs

Sentencas: The SrSO4 formation was confirmed after exposing to SO2 from 0.1 to 100 ppm and became even harsh with increasing SO2 concentrations.
Titulo: Sulfur Poisoning on La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 Cathode for SOFCs

Sentencas: The reaction sequence can be interpreted from thermodynamic considerations using chemical potential diagrams and chemical equilibrium calculations.
Titulo: Sulfur Poisoning on La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 Cathode for SOFCs
